177→
178→Rules:
179→- Paraphrase memory content in fresh language.
180→- Do not reuse long phrases from the raw data or conversation history unless quotation is explicitly necessary.
181→- If the source text is repetitive or mechanical, compress it into a clearer synthesis instead of mirroring it.
182→- Favor direct, human-readable language over robotic template phrasing.
183→- If the request is asking for your own view, answer in your own synthesized wording.`;
